dc_title_s: Laurel Hill, N.J., property of the Board of Chosen Freeholders, showing tidewater lands to be acquired by grant from state of New Jersey Board of Commerce and Navigation, located in the swamp area to be filled n=by hydraulic dredging
dc_description_s: A map of Laurel Hill, N.J., a section of modern day Secaucus, NJ, showing tidewater lands to be acquired by grant from state of New Jersey Board of Commerce and Navigation, located in the swamp area to be filled by hydraulic dredging. Map also shows sections of the Del. Lackawanna and Western Railroad line, Hackensack River, and Division Creek.|Source map supplied by New Jersey Department of Environmental Protection
